: The great mistake,&rdquo; <em>Fortune<\/em>, 03\/22\/2006, http:\/\/archive.fortune.com\/2006\/03\/09\/magazines\/fortune\/cubicle_howiwork_fortune\/index.htm<a href=&quot;#ref34\&quot; title=\"Jump back to footnote 34 in the text.\">\u21a9<\/a>","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_003535.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":"212.642578125","resource_grade_level":"","resource_curriculum":"","resource_tour":"","resource_file_time":"00m 00s","resource_file_time_unformatted":"0","resource_source_detail":"\"Tools of the Trade: 19th- and 20th-Century Architectural Trade Catalogs,\" Case 6, Ryerson &amp; Burnham Libraries, August 4, 2015-October 12, 2015.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<a href=&quot;https:\/\/digital-libraries.artic.edu\/cdm\/ref\/collection\/mqc\/id\/68796&quot;>Link to R&amp;B Archives Digital Collections record<\/a>","resource_tags_for_resource_id":"architecture"},"resource_3536":{"resource_link":"..\/3536","resource_url":"http:\/\/www.artic.edu\/aic\/collections\/citi\/resources\/Rsrc_003536.jpg","resource_title":"02. \"Arnot Introduces 'A New Way of Life' in the Office.\" Swan Equipment Company; Buffalo, NY; 1954.","resource_description":"The significant rise in the number of technical and professional staff employed by modern businesses demanded offices with greater privacy and improved acoustics, lighting and climate control, while increased competitiveness necessitated efficient, flexible and simple products that could be reused with little cost. These proto-cubicles by Arnot were marketed as a &ldquo;private office-ettes.&rdquo;","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_003536.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":